1
00:00:02,544 --> 00:00:06,590
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,
SEPTEMBER 18, 2152.

2
00:00:06,632 --> 00:00:09,844
WE'VE ENTERED ORBIT
OF AN UNINHABITED PLANET.

3
00:00:09,885 --> 00:00:11,178
OUR SCANS SHOW IT'S TEEMING

4
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:13,889
WITH ALL SORTS OF PLANT
AND ANIMAL LIFE.

5
00:00:13,931 --> 00:00:16,809
I'LL BE LEADING A SURVEY TEAM
TO THE SURFACE.

6
00:00:16,851 --> 00:00:18,644
TUCKER: THERE'S A GORGE
ON THE SOUTHERN CONTINENT

7
00:00:18,686 --> 00:00:20,646
FIVE TIMES DEEPER
THAN THE GRAND CANYON.

8
00:00:20,688 --> 00:00:22,189
ARCHER: WHAT HAVE YOU
GOT IN MIND?

9
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:24,232
TUCKER: HOW ABOUT A LITTLE
RIVER RAFTING?

10
00:00:24,274 --> 00:00:26,568
T'POL SAYS IT ONLY GETS
DARK FOUR DAYS A MONTH

11
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:28,236
BECAUSE OF THE BINARY SUNS.

12
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:29,655
WE'LL HAVE PLENTY
OF DAYLIGHT LEFT

13
00:00:29,697 --> 00:00:31,072
AFTER WE'RE DONE
WORKING EVERY NIGHT.

14
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:32,574
ARCHER: IT'S GOING TO TAKE
AT LEAST A WEEK

15
00:00:32,616 --> 00:00:33,868
TO COMPLETE THE SURVEY.

16
00:00:33,909 --> 00:00:35,494
SHOULD BE ENOUGH TIME
TO SNEAK IN SOME R&amp;R.

17
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:37,329
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
T'Pol: Bridge to Captain Archer.

18
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:38,706
GO AHEAD.

19
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:40,332
T'Pol: We've got an alien vessel
approaching.

20
00:00:40,374 --> 00:00:41,625
They're hailing us.

21
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,251
ARCHER: PUT THEM THROUGH
TO<i> SHUTTLEPOD 1.</i>

22
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:44,670
T'Pol: Yes, sir.

23
00:00:44,712 --> 00:00:48,131
TUCKER: NEW PLANET,
NEW ALIENS...BANNER DAY.

24
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:50,342
<i>WE'RE VERY RELIEVED</i>
<i>TO SEE YOU.</i>

25
00:00:50,384 --> 00:00:52,260
<i>I'M RELLUS TAGRIM.</i>
<i>THIS IS MY CREW.</i>

26
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:55,472
ARCHER: CAPTAIN ARCHER OF
THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

27
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:56,682
SOMETHING WE CAN DO FOR YOU?

28
00:00:56,724 --> 00:00:58,308
<i>CONSIDERING</i>
<i>THE CIRCUMSTANCES,</i>

29
00:00:58,350 --> 00:01:00,019
<i>WE WOULD LIKE PERMISSION</i>
<i>TO COME ABOARD</i>

30
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,646
<i>AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.</i>

31
00:01:02,688 --> 00:01:04,523
ARCHER: WHAT CIRCUMSTANCES?

32
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:08,235
<i>THE NEUTRONIC WAVE FRONT...</i>
<i>IT'S ALMOST HERE.</i>

33
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:10,237
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

34
00:01:10,278 --> 00:01:11,822
TUCKER: NOTHING ON SENSORS.

35
00:01:11,864 --> 00:01:13,782
<i>TAGRIM: YOU SHOULD DETECT</i>
<i>THE STORM IN A FEW MINUTES.</i>

36
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:15,450
<i>IT'S TRAVELING AT HIGH WARP.</i>

37
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:16,911
<i>ONCE WE'RE ABOARD,</i>

38
00:01:16,952 --> 00:01:19,914
<i>I SUGGEST THAT YOU GO</i>
<i>TO WARP 7 IMMEDIATELY.</i>

39
00:01:22,207 --> 00:01:25,377
ARCHER: OUR TOP SPEED IS WARP 5.

40
00:01:28,047 --> 00:01:32,634
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

41
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:35,888
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

42
00:01:35,930 --> 00:01:39,767
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

43
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:43,311
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

44
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:47,816
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

45
00:01:47,858 --> 00:01:51,278
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

46
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:55,282
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

47
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:58,410
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

48
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:01,121
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

49
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:03,290
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

50
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:06,209
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

51
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:11,048
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

52
00:02:11,090 --> 00:02:14,301
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

53
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:18,555
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

54
00:02:18,597 --> 00:02:21,767
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

55
00:02:21,809 --> 00:02:27,397
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

56
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:29,441
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

57
00:02:29,483 --> 00:02:31,735
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

58
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:35,322
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

59
00:02:35,363 --> 00:02:40,119
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

60
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:54,424
T'POL: THE WAVE FRONT SPANS MORE
THAN HALF A DOZEN LIGHT YEARS.

61
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:56,844
A VULCAN STARSHIP
ENCOUNTERED A CLASS-5

62
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:58,345
OVER A CENTURY AGO.

63
00:02:58,386 --> 00:03:03,308
THE VESSEL WAS...
NEARLY DESTROYED.

64
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:05,477
ARCHER: HOW LONG UNTIL IT HITS?

65
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:08,229
T'POL: APPROXIMATELY FOUR HOURS.

66
00:03:08,271 --> 00:03:10,607
REED: IF WE REINFORCE
STRUCTURAL INTEGRITY,

67
00:03:10,649 --> 00:03:12,943
WE SHOULD BE ABLE TO WEATHER IT
WITHOUT TOO MUCH TROUBLE.

68
00:03:12,985 --> 00:03:14,862
PHLOX:<i> ENTERPRISE</i> MAY SURVIVE.

69
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:16,530
THE CREW IS ANOTHER MATTER.

70
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:20,241
THE STORM IS SATURATED
WITH RADIOLYTIC ISOTOPES.

71
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:21,827
IF THE CREW IS EXPOSED,

72
00:03:21,869 --> 00:03:24,412
THEY'LL BE DEAD
WITHIN THREE MINUTES.

73
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:26,748
SICKBAY IS THE MOST
HEAVILY SHIELDED SECTION.

74
00:03:26,790 --> 00:03:29,043
IT'S POSSIBLE THAT SOME
OF THE CREW COULD SURVIVE THERE.

75
00:03:29,084 --> 00:03:31,003
ARCHER: WE CAN'T FIT 83 PEOPLE
INTO SICKBAY,

76
00:03:31,045 --> 00:03:33,672
AND I'M NOT ABOUT TO DRAW LOTS.

77
00:03:34,631 --> 00:03:36,508
WHAT ABOUT THE CATWALK?

78
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,177
YOU KNOW,
THE MAINTENANCE SHAFT

79
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:40,303
RUNNING THE LENGTH
OF EACH NACELLE.

80
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:45,308
ARCHER: THEY ARE
HEAVILY SHIELDED...

81
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:49,354
SOME KIND OF OSMIUM ALLOY,
IF I REMEMBER.

82
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:52,858
YOU'RE PROPOSING WE TAKE REFUGE
IN A CRAWLSPACE?

83
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,526
IT'LL BE A TIGHT SQUEEZE,

84
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:56,945
BUT THERE'S NO REASON
WE CAN'T FIT 83 PEOPLE IN THERE,

85
00:03:56,987 --> 00:03:58,864
AND WHATEVER SUPPLIES WE NEED.

86
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:00,365
DOCTOR?

87
00:04:00,407 --> 00:04:02,450
PHLOX: DO YOU KNOW THE
ABSORPTION DEPTH OF THIS ALLOY?

88
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:05,162
AT LEAST 20,000 PARTICLES
PER MICRON.

89
00:04:05,204 --> 00:04:07,081
PHLOX: IT SHOULD BE ADEQUATE.

90
00:04:07,122 --> 00:04:08,957
TUCKER: THERE'S JUST
ONE OTHER PROBLEM.

91
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:10,667
IT GETS KIND OF TOASTY IN THERE

92
00:04:10,709 --> 00:04:12,502
WHEN THE WARP COILS
ARE ON LINE...

93
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:14,254
ABOUT 300 DEGREES.

94
00:04:14,295 --> 00:04:17,424
WE'D HAVE TO SHUT DOWN
THE MAIN REACTOR.

95
00:04:20,427 --> 00:04:23,388
ARCHER: I DON'T SEE
THAT WE HAVE ANY CHOICE.

96
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:26,141
WE'LL USE THE CATWALK.

97
00:04:26,183 --> 00:04:29,186
AND SET UP A COMMAND STATION
IN ONE OF THE COMPARTMENTS.

98
00:04:29,228 --> 00:04:31,271
AYE, CAPTAIN.

99
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:34,024
ARCHER: YOU'LL BE IN CHARGE
OF THE EVACUATION.

100
00:04:34,066 --> 00:04:37,069
TAKE US OUT OF ORBIT, TRAVIS.

101
00:04:56,755 --> 00:04:58,381
MAYWEATHER: MAYBE WE SHOULD
OPEN A WINDOW.

102
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:00,008
TUCKER: YOU THINK
IT'S STUFFY NOW,

103
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:02,385
WAIT TILL WE GET 83 PEOPLE
IN HERE.

104
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:06,598
MAYWEATHER: DON'T FORGET PORTHOS
AND ALL THE DOCTOR'S ANIMALS.

105
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:09,017
YOU EVER BEEN THROUGH A STORM
AS BAD AS THIS?

106
00:05:09,059 --> 00:05:10,685
MAYWEATHER: WE RAN INTO
A CLASS-3 ONCE,

107
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:12,854
HAD TO TAKE SHELTER
IN THE SHIP'S CORE.

108
00:05:12,896 --> 00:05:14,481
WE WERE DOWN THERE
FOR SIX WEEKS.

109
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:17,276
TUCKER: SIX WEEKS?

110
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:20,112
MAYWEATHER: ANY IDEA
ABOUT A LATRINE?

111
00:05:20,154 --> 00:05:22,656
TUCKER: OH, I NEVER THOUGHT
ABOUT THAT.

112
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:24,866
THERE ARE SOME STORAGE LOCKERS
IN THE AFT COMPARTMENT.

113
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:27,995
WE OUGHT TO BE ABLE TO
CONVERT A COUPLE OF THEM.

114
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:45,846
TUCKER: THIS'LL BE OUR BRIDGE.

115
00:05:49,183 --> 00:05:51,685
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO JURY-RIG THESE PANELS,

116
00:05:51,726 --> 00:05:53,937
TAP THEM INTO COMMAND FUNCTIONS.

117
00:05:53,979 --> 00:05:57,274
MAYWEATHER: NOT MUCH ROOM
FOR A CAPTAIN'S CHAIR.

118
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,611
THAT STORM
MUST'VE BEEN PRETTY SCARY.

119
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:04,239
WE ONLY GOT WORRIED
WHEN THE GENERATORS WENT DOWN.

120
00:06:04,281 --> 00:06:07,534
WE LOST THE GRAV-PLATING,
LIFE SUPPORT...

121
00:06:07,575 --> 00:06:11,830
I'LL NEVER FORGET THAT LOOK
IN MY FATHER'S EYES.

122
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:15,458
HE KNEW WE WERE IN TROUBLE.

123
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,384
[ SNIFFS ]

124
00:06:27,554 --> 00:06:30,182
ARCHER: SORRY TO KEEP YOU
IN THERE SO LONG.

125
00:06:30,224 --> 00:06:31,474
PLEASE.

126
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:34,186
WE UNDERSTAND.

127
00:06:34,228 --> 00:06:35,854
ARCHER: MY SCIENCE OFFICER
TELLS ME

128
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:37,605
YOU'RE FROM THE TAKRET SYSTEM.

129
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,524
THAT'S A LONG WAY FROM HERE.

130
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:42,194
TAGRIM: OUR WORK OFTEN
TAKES US FAR FROM HOME.

131
00:06:42,236 --> 00:06:44,196
TAKRETI: WE'RE STELLAR
CARTOGRAPHERS.

132
00:06:44,238 --> 00:06:45,864
ARCHER: REALLY?

133
00:06:45,906 --> 00:06:47,824
ONCE WE GET OUT OF THE STORM,

134
00:06:47,866 --> 00:06:50,785
MAYBE YOU COULD HELP US
UPDATE OUR STAR CHARTS.

135
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,163
TAGRIM: WE'D BE PLEASED.

136
00:06:53,205 --> 00:06:55,332
PHLOX: THIS WAY.

137
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:02,381
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

138
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:39,834
T'POL: YOU'RE BEHIND SCHEDULE.
DO YOU NEED HELP?

139
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:42,296
PHLOX: I UNDERSTAND YOU'VE
ALLOTTED 15 CUBIC METERS

140
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:44,839
FOR MEDICAL SUPPLIES?

141
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:46,174
T'POL: THAT'S CORRECT.

142
00:07:46,216 --> 00:07:47,926
THAT MEANS
THERE'S ONLY ENOUGH ROOM

143
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:49,928
FOR TWO THIRDS OF THESE CAGES.

144
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:52,264
[ T'POL INHALES ]

145
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:56,143
T'POL: PERHAPS SOME OF
YOUR CREATURES COULD SHARE.

146
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:58,270
PHLOX: THEY'LL EAT EACH OTHER.

147
00:07:58,312 --> 00:08:02,774
THEY'RE VITAL TO MY WORK
AND THE HEALTH OF THIS CREW.

148
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:08,655
I'M NOT ACCUSTOMED
TO MAKING EMOTIONAL APPEALS.

149
00:08:08,696 --> 00:08:12,659
PLEASE...DON'T ASK ME
TO CHOOSE BETWEEN THEM.

150
00:08:14,869 --> 00:08:17,205
T'POL: ALL RIGHT.

151
00:08:17,247 --> 00:08:20,459
20 CUBIC METERS.

152
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,503
MY EDOSIAN SLUGS THANK YOU.

153
00:08:27,299 --> 00:08:28,758
TUCKER: I'M--I'M AFRAID

154
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,470
THESE AREN'T
FIRST-CLASS ACCOMMODATIONS.

155
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:34,348
TAGRIM: THEY'LL BE FINE,
COMMANDER.

156
00:08:34,389 --> 00:08:36,850
WE'RE GRATEFUL
FOR YOUR HOSPITALITY.

157
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:38,435
TUCKER: WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
A LOT OF TIME

158
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:40,770
TO GET TO KNOW EACH OTHER.

159
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:45,025
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING,
I'LL BE RIGHT OVER HERE.

160
00:08:47,319 --> 00:08:49,821
TAKRETI: I DON'T KNOW THE FIRST
THING ABOUT STELLAR CARTOGRAPHY.

161
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:51,072
TAGRIM: GURI--

162
00:08:51,114 --> 00:08:53,492
GURI: WHAT IF THEY BEGIN
TO ASK QUESTIONS?

163
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:13,136
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

164
00:09:13,178 --> 00:09:14,971
COME IN.

165
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:22,020
I DIDN'T EXPECT IT
TO BE BEAUTIFUL.

166
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:28,276
ARCHER: TOO BAD WE DON'T
HAVE TIME TO RUN SOME SCANS.

167
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:30,237
T'POL: WE'LL BE
INSIDE THE PHENOMENON

168
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:32,697
FOR NEARLY EIGHT DAYS.

169
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:35,242
WE CAN RUN ALL
THE SCANS WE WANT.

170
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:39,329
LIEUTENANT REED HAS COMPLETED
HIS MODIFICATIONS.

171
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:44,125
ARCHER: I'M A LITTLE NERVOUS
ABOUT SHUTTING DOWN

172
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:45,502
THE POWER GRID.

173
00:09:45,544 --> 00:09:48,088
A SINGLE NEUTRONIC SURGE
COULD OVERLOAD THE GRID

174
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:51,258
AND DAMAGE CRITICAL SYSTEMS.

175
00:09:56,346 --> 00:09:59,599
ARCHER: I DID A LITTLE RESEARCH
IN THE VULCAN DATABASE.

176
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:03,103
THAT CLASS-5 STORM
A CENTURY AGO...

177
00:10:03,144 --> 00:10:06,273
INVOLVED THE STARSHIP<i> T'PLANA.</i>

178
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:09,359
APPARENTLY, THEY COULDN'T
OUTRUN THE WAVE FRONT.

179
00:10:09,401 --> 00:10:13,154
IT WAS LOST WITH ALL HANDS.

180
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:19,869
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
IT WAS<i> NEARLY</i> DESTROYED.

181
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:27,377
I MUST HAVE REMEMBERED
INCORRECTLY.

182
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:39,639
BRIDGE TO COMMANDER TUCKER.

183
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,848
Tucker: Go ahead.

184
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:42,225
READY FOR THE HANDOFF?

185
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:44,018
GIVE ME A SECOND.

186
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:00,160
TUCKER: STANDING BY, CAPTAIN.

187
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,918
[ BEEPING ]

188
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:13,465
TUCKER: WE'RE IN
THE DRIVER'S SEAT.

189
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:16,593
SEE YOU IN A FEW MINUTES.
ARCHER OUT.

190
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,597
LET'S CLOSE UP SHOP.

191
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:55,632
ARCHER: YOU DONE A HEAD COUNT?

192
00:11:55,674 --> 00:11:58,801
THE ENTIRE CREW'S ACCOUNTED FOR,
INCLUDING ONE QUADRUPED.

193
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:01,971
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TRY OUT
THE CAPTAIN'S CHAIR?

194
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:04,224
ARCHER: MAYBE LATER.

195
00:12:10,522 --> 00:12:12,524
WHERE'S THE COM?

196
00:12:13,983 --> 00:12:15,734
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

197
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:17,945
ALL HANDS, THIS IS THE CAPTAIN.

198
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:20,699
This catwalk is going
to be our home for a while--

199
00:12:20,739 --> 00:12:22,741
a week, maybe more.

200
00:12:22,783 --> 00:12:26,745
You may not be comfortable,
but you'll be alive.

201
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:30,917
We have the best crew in the
fleet and the sturdiest ship.

202
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:34,962
I promise you,
we'll get through this.

203
00:12:41,553 --> 00:12:43,221
ARCHER: TIME?

204
00:12:43,263 --> 00:12:45,557
ONE MINUTE, FIVE SECONDS.

205
00:12:45,599 --> 00:12:47,850
POLARIZE THE HULL PLATING.

206
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:59,028
30 SECONDS.

207
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:02,031
[ RUMBLING ]

208
00:13:02,073 --> 00:13:03,866
TRAVIS?

209
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:06,119
SPATIAL TURBULENCE.

210
00:13:08,663 --> 00:13:10,749
20 SECONDS.

211
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:16,504
T'POL: 15.

212
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:20,049
10.

213
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:24,763
ALL HANDS, BRACE FOR IMPACT.

214
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:36,941
MAYWEATHER: AFT STABILIZERS
AREN'T ENGAGING.

215
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:38,777
TRY THEM AGAIN!

216
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:54,125
GRAV-SHEAR'S DROPPING.

217
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:01,257
THAT SHOULD BE
THE WORST OF IT, SIR...

218
00:14:01,299 --> 00:14:03,718
AT LEAST FOR NOW.

219
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:27,908
ARCHER: YOURS?

220
00:14:30,537 --> 00:14:32,955
LOOKS LIKE
YOU'RE ALMOST FINISHED.

221
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:38,127
YOU WOULDN'T KNOW
WHO WAS THE FIRST

222
00:14:38,169 --> 00:14:40,254
VULCAN AMBASSADOR TO EARTH?

223
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,298
SIX LETTERS, ENDS WITH AN R?

224
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:44,843
SOLKAR...I THINK.

225
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:46,886
THANKS, CAPTAIN.

226
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:49,972
DON'T MENTION IT.

227
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:54,227
[ SIGHS ]

228
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:01,901
-HOW YOU HOLDING UP?
-PRETTY WELL, SIR.

229
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:03,944
A FEW DAYS IN THIS PLACE
SHOULD CURE ANYONE

230
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:05,864
OF CLAUSTROPHOBIA.

231
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:09,534
YOUR QUARTERS WILL PROBABLY FEEL
LIKE A BALLROOM AFTER THIS.

232
00:15:13,872 --> 00:15:15,289
YOU'RE THE CAPTAIN.

233
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:17,917
CAN'T YOU ORDER THE STORM
TO CALM DOWN A LITTLE?

234
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:20,420
I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN DO.

235
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:26,050
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

236
00:15:49,407 --> 00:15:50,867
HOW ARE THEY DOING?

237
00:15:50,909 --> 00:15:53,828
WELL, YOUR GUESS
IS AS GOOD AS MINE.

238
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:55,705
ONE OF THEM CAME OUT
A FEW HOURS AGO,

239
00:15:55,747 --> 00:15:59,041
TOLD US WE WERE MAKING
TOO MUCH NOISE.

240
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,960
AND I'VE BEEN REAL FRIENDLY...

241
00:16:01,001 --> 00:16:03,170
EVEN ASKED THEM
TO JOIN THE GAME.

242
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:06,048
DOESN'T SEEM LIKE THEY WANT
TO HAVE ANYTHING TO DO WITH US.

243
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:11,512
LET'S GIVE THEM
A LITTLE TIME TO ADJUST.

244
00:16:11,554 --> 00:16:13,514
YOU KNOW, I BET BY NOW
WE'D HAVE SET UP CAMP

245
00:16:13,556 --> 00:16:15,141
ON THE RIM OF THAT CANYON...

246
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:17,351
HAD A FIRE GOING.

247
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:19,771
THERE'LL BE OTHER CANYONS.

248
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:33,200
PHLOX: LIEUTENANT,
ARE YOU PASSING THROUGH,

249
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:35,662
OR IS THERE SOMETHING
I CAN HELP YOU WITH?

250
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:38,038
REED: ACTUALLY,
THERE IS SOMETHING.

251
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,540
PHLOX: YES?

252
00:16:39,582 --> 00:16:42,168
REED: AHEM.

253
00:16:43,962 --> 00:16:47,674
I ASSUME I CAN DEPEND ON
DOCTOR-PATIENT CONFIDENTIALITY.

254
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:49,300
PHLOX: THIS WOULDN'T
HAVE ANYTHING TO DO

255
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:51,552
WITH GASTROINTESTINAL
DISTRESS?

256
00:16:51,594 --> 00:16:53,429
IS IT THAT OBVIOUS?

257
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:54,764
PHLOX: NOT AT ALL.

258
00:16:54,806 --> 00:16:56,516
THERE'S A NOTATION
IN YOUR MEDICAL FILE,

259
00:16:56,557 --> 00:17:00,770
SOMETHING ABOUT AN UNFORTUNATE
INCIDENT DURING ZERO-G TRAINING?

260
00:17:00,812 --> 00:17:02,981
THE E.V. SIMULATOR AT LUNAPORT,

261
00:17:03,063 --> 00:17:06,359
OR AS STARFLEET TRAINEES
CALL IT, THE VOMITORIUM.

262
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,486
PHLOX: NOTHING TO BE
EMBARRASSED ABOUT.

263
00:17:08,528 --> 00:17:10,404
I'VE TREATED A NUMBER OF CREWMEN

264
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:13,324
THIS AFTERNOON
FOR MOTION SICKNESS.

265
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:16,160
THAT SHOULD LAST
FOR ABOUT 12 HOURS.

266
00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:18,496
OH. THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

267
00:17:18,538 --> 00:17:20,373
ARCHER: FEELING ALL RIGHT,
MALCOLM?

268
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:23,543
REED: UH...NEVER BETTER.

269
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:31,676
ANY PROBLEMS WITH THE CREW?

270
00:17:31,718 --> 00:17:33,845
OH, A FEW BUMPS AND BRUISES
FROM THE TURBULENCE.

271
00:17:33,887 --> 00:17:36,514
NOTHING TOO SERIOUS.

272
00:17:36,556 --> 00:17:39,099
ARCHER: I COULD SEE ABOUT
MOVING SOME OF THIS

273
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:40,560
TO THE AFT SECTION.

274
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:43,270
NONSENSE!
I HAVE PLENTY OF ROOM.

275
00:17:43,312 --> 00:17:45,356
I FIND THE CLOSE QUARTERS
RATHER COMFORTING.

276
00:17:45,398 --> 00:17:47,233
IT REMINDS ME OF HOME.

277
00:17:47,274 --> 00:17:50,236
I DIDN'T REALIZE SPACE
WAS AT A PREMIUM ON DENOBULA.

278
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:53,113
12 BILLION PEOPLE SHARING
ONE CONTINENT.

279
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:56,534
LET ME KNOW
IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND.

280
00:17:57,493 --> 00:18:00,621
[ HATCH OPENS ]

281
00:18:00,663 --> 00:18:02,540
TRAVIS?

282
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:04,458
MAYWEATHER: WE'VE GOT A CLUSTER
OF PLASMA EDDIES

283
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,627
ABOUT 80,000 KILOMETERS AHEAD.

284
00:18:06,669 --> 00:18:08,337
I SHOULD BE ABLE
TO STEER CLEAR OF THEM.

285
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:09,881
ARCHER: WAKE ME
IF THERE'S A PROBLEM.

286
00:18:09,923 --> 00:18:11,090
MAYWEATHER: AYE, CAPTAIN.

287
00:18:11,131 --> 00:18:12,633
ARCHER: WHEN WE'RE PAST
THOSE EDDIES,

288
00:18:12,675 --> 00:18:14,260
TRY AND GET SOME REST YOURSELF.

289
00:18:14,301 --> 00:18:15,887
ENSIGN TANNER CAN RELIEVE YOU.

290
00:18:15,929 --> 00:18:17,263
THANK YOU, SIR.

291
00:18:17,304 --> 00:18:19,933
-GOOD NIGHT.
-NIGHT.

292
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:29,067
ARCHER: HEY. HEY.

293
00:18:34,072 --> 00:18:37,199
GO ON. GO TO SLEEP.

294
00:18:47,752 --> 00:18:49,796
YEAH.

295
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:53,591
PHEW.

296
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:55,009
OH!

297
00:18:55,051 --> 00:18:57,011
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

298
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:00,640
IS THIS BOTHERING YOU?

299
00:19:00,681 --> 00:19:03,309
T'POL: ONLY SLIGHTLY.

300
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:11,859
[ PADD TURNS OFF ]

301
00:19:11,901 --> 00:19:15,488
[ PADD BEEPING ]

302
00:19:24,371 --> 00:19:25,957
AM I DISTURBING YOU?

303
00:19:25,999 --> 00:19:28,542
ONLY SLIGHTLY.

304
00:19:39,971 --> 00:19:42,682
ARCHER: YOU KNOW, THERE'S
A BRIGHT SIDE TO ALL OF THIS.

305
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:44,183
REALLY?

306
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:47,353
IT'S BRINGING THE CREW
CLOSER TOGETHER.

307
00:19:47,394 --> 00:19:49,730
IF YOU FORGET
ABOUT THE STORM OUTSIDE,

308
00:19:49,772 --> 00:19:52,525
THIS IS ALMOST LIKE GOING
ON A CAMPING TRIP.

309
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:57,030
PERHAPS WE CAN SING
A FEW SONGS LATER.

310
00:19:58,531 --> 00:20:01,075
ARCHER: HAVEN'T YOU EVER
GONE CAMPING?

311
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,999
IN A MANNER OF SPEAKING.

312
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:11,961
I ONCE PARTICIPATED
IN THE<i> KAHS-WAN</i> RITUAL.

313
00:20:12,003 --> 00:20:15,589
I WAS TAKEN TO THE DESERT
AND LEFT TO SURVIVE FOR 10 DAYS.

314
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:17,925
SOUNDS FUN.

315
00:20:20,803 --> 00:20:25,975
YOU...HAVEN'T LEFT
THE COMMAND AREA MUCH TODAY.

316
00:20:26,017 --> 00:20:29,020
YOU MIGHT WANT TO WANDER AROUND,
GET TO KNOW THE CREW.

317
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:31,064
I'M FAMILIAR
WITH EVERY ONE OF THEM.

318
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:34,650
THERE'S A LOT MORE TO THESE
PEOPLE THAN JUST THEIR NAMES.

319
00:20:34,692 --> 00:20:38,529
IT'D BE GOOD FOR YOU
TO FRATERNIZE A LITTLE.

320
00:20:38,571 --> 00:20:41,281
IS THAT AN ORDER?

321
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:44,202
DOES IT HAVE TO BE?

322
00:20:49,749 --> 00:20:53,544
I'M NOT SKILLED
AT FRATERNIZING.

323
00:20:58,298 --> 00:21:00,676
HERE'S A CHANCE TO LEARN.

324
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:13,856
REED: I'LL SEE YOUR STRAWBERRY
SHORTCAKE...

325
00:21:13,898 --> 00:21:18,861
AND I'LL RAISE YOU
ONE PINEAPPLE COBBLER.

326
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:28,121
-BROCCOLI?
-I'M OUT OF DESSERTS.

327
00:21:28,162 --> 00:21:29,663
MAYWEATHER: CALL.

328
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:32,499
OH, WHAT I WOULDN'T GIVE
FOR A SHOWER RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

329
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:34,334
WHEN THIS HAND'S OVER,

330
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:36,921
MAYBE YOU COULD LOOK
INTO BUILDING ONE.

331
00:21:36,963 --> 00:21:38,881
WOULD YOU LIKE A SAUNA
WHILE I'M AT IT?

332
00:21:38,923 --> 00:21:40,258
[ CHUCKLES ]

333
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:42,885
YOU KNEW WE'D BE STUCK
IN HERE FOR OVER A WEEK.

334
00:21:42,927 --> 00:21:45,554
YOU MIGHT'VE GIVEN A LITTLE
THOUGHT TO MAKING IT TOLERABLE.

335
00:21:45,596 --> 00:21:48,307
I ONLY HAD FOUR HOURS, MALCOLM.

336
00:21:48,348 --> 00:21:50,268
YOU'RE LUCKY WE'VE GOT A TOILET.

337
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:52,645
WELL, I OBVIOUSLY OVERESTIMATED
YOUR PEOPLE'S ABILITIES

338
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:55,106
WHEN IT COMES
TO INDOOR PLUMBING.

339
00:21:55,148 --> 00:21:57,275
YOU WANT TO TAKE A SHOWER?

340
00:21:57,316 --> 00:21:59,277
BUILD ONE YOURSELF.

341
00:22:01,154 --> 00:22:04,406
-THANKS, CHEF.
-THANKS, CHEF.

342
00:22:04,448 --> 00:22:06,075
REED: POT ROAST?

343
00:22:06,117 --> 00:22:07,285
OH, COME ON.

344
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:09,495
THAT'S THE THIRD TIME
IN THREE DAYS!

345
00:22:09,536 --> 00:22:12,331
AH!

346
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:14,416
MAYWEATHER: ANYONE KNOW
WHAT THEY'RE SHOWING TONIGHT?

347
00:22:14,458 --> 00:22:16,210
"THE DAY THE EARTH STOOD STILL."

348
00:22:16,252 --> 00:22:18,754
WE'RE HAVING MOVIE NIGHT
IN HERE?

349
00:22:18,796 --> 00:22:20,380
CAPTAIN'S ORDERS.

350
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:22,216
I SET UP A MONITOR
IN COMPARTMENT 5.

351
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:23,550
THE SCREEN'S
A LITTLE SMALL, BUT...

352
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:25,219
WHO'S PICKING THESE MOVIES?

353
00:22:25,261 --> 00:22:27,638
SHOULDN'T WE ALL GET A VOTE?

354
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:30,224
I THINK SOMETHING'S BURNING.

355
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:36,354
TUCKER: ARE YOU AWARE
YOU'RE SITTING ON TOP OF

356
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:37,606
A PLASMA MANIFOLD?

357
00:22:37,648 --> 00:22:39,233
YOU GOT TO TURN THAT THING OFF!

358
00:22:39,275 --> 00:22:41,777
[ SIZZLING ]

359
00:22:41,819 --> 00:22:43,112
TAGRIM: I APOLOGIZE, COMMANDER.

360
00:22:43,154 --> 00:22:45,114
WE SHOULD'VE SPOKEN
WITH YOU FIRST.

361
00:22:45,156 --> 00:22:46,949
TUCKER: THAT MIGHT'VE BEEN
A GOOD IDEA.

362
00:22:46,991 --> 00:22:49,493
TAKRETI: WE'VE HAD TROUBLE
DIGESTING YOUR FOOD.

363
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:52,038
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]
Archer: Archer to Tucker.

364
00:22:54,581 --> 00:22:55,958
TUCKER: GO AHEAD.

365
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,877
Archer: I need you
in the command area right away.

366
00:22:57,918 --> 00:23:00,671
TUCKER: I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

367
00:23:00,713 --> 00:23:02,256
I'LL TALK TO CHEF.

368
00:23:02,298 --> 00:23:04,175
MAYBE HE CAN...

369
00:23:04,217 --> 00:23:07,011
HEAT THAT UP FOR YOU.

370
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:19,023
WE MAY HAVE A PROBLEM
IN ENGINEERING.

371
00:23:19,065 --> 00:23:21,150
THE ANTIMATTER INJECTORS
HAVE COME ON LINE.

372
00:23:21,192 --> 00:23:22,818
THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT.

373
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:25,863
PROBABLY JUST A GLITCH.

374
00:23:25,905 --> 00:23:28,782
THINK YOU'VE GOT ROOM FOR ONE
MORE SLEEPING BAG IN HERE?

375
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:31,535
ARCHER: NOT HAPPY
WITH YOUR BUNKMATES?

376
00:23:31,577 --> 00:23:33,287
I CAUGHT THEM
THROWING A BARBECUE

377
00:23:33,329 --> 00:23:34,788
NEXT TO A PLASMA MANIFOLD.

378
00:23:34,830 --> 00:23:36,623
NOW, I UNDERSTAND
WE'RE EXPLORERS--

379
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:38,125
WE'RE SUPPOSED
TO KEEP AN OPEN MIND

380
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:39,501
ABOUT DIFFERENT CULTURES,

381
00:23:39,543 --> 00:23:41,379
BUT THESE GUYS
ARE DRIVING ME CRAZY.

382
00:23:41,419 --> 00:23:43,297
THEY ONLY NEED
TO SLEEP ONCE A WEEK.

383
00:23:43,339 --> 00:23:44,840
SO THEY'VE KEPT US UP
THE LAST TWO NIGHTS

384
00:23:44,882 --> 00:23:46,675
WITH THEIR STRANGE RITUALS--

385
00:23:46,717 --> 00:23:49,845
CHANTING, WALKING IN CIRCLES.

386
00:23:49,887 --> 00:23:52,265
THEY'VE PRACTICALLY TAKEN
OVER THE COMPARTMENT!

387
00:23:52,306 --> 00:23:54,934
DON'T FORGET THEY'RE THE ONES
WHO WARNED US ABOUT THE STORM.

388
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:57,228
WE OWE THEM.

389
00:23:57,270 --> 00:23:58,229
BE PATIENT.

390
00:23:58,271 --> 00:24:01,481
I'M TRYING.

391
00:24:04,318 --> 00:24:05,903
TUCKER: LOOKS LIKE
THE MATTER INJECTORS

392
00:24:05,945 --> 00:24:08,030
AND THE ANTIMATTER INJECTORS
ARE ON LINE.

393
00:24:08,072 --> 00:24:10,157
TWO SENSOR GLITCHES?

394
00:24:10,199 --> 00:24:13,369
T'POL: A POWER SURGE COULD HAVE
TRIGGERED BOTH CIRCUITS.

395
00:24:13,411 --> 00:24:15,037
TUCKER: DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT THE ODDS ARE

396
00:24:15,079 --> 00:24:16,122
OF THAT HAPPENING?

397
00:24:16,163 --> 00:24:18,456
CAN YOU SHUT THEM DOWN?

398
00:24:18,498 --> 00:24:21,168
TUCKER: NOT FROM HERE.

399
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:27,425
SOMEONE'S GONNA HAVE
TO GO TO ENGINEERING.

400
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:39,519
PHLOX: REMEMBER, THE SUIT WILL
PROTECT YOU FOR ONLY 22 MINUTES.

401
00:24:43,441 --> 00:24:48,112
IT'D BE BEST NOT TO TAKE
THE SCENIC ROUTE.

402
00:25:37,328 --> 00:25:39,788
[ DOOR LATCH CLANGS ]

403
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:47,421
[ FOOTSTEPS DESCENDING ]

404
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:41,517
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

405
00:27:01,703 --> 00:27:03,581
[ DOOR OPENING ]

406
00:28:11,649 --> 00:28:13,108
TAKRETI: WE'VE SEARCHED
EVERY DECK.

407
00:28:13,150 --> 00:28:14,652
THERE'S NO SIGN
OF THE FUGITIVES.

408
00:28:14,692 --> 00:28:16,278
WHAT ABOUT THE CREW?

409
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:18,572
IT APPEARS THEY
HAVE DESERTED THE SHIP.

410
00:28:18,614 --> 00:28:21,450
THESE HUMANS...

411
00:28:21,492 --> 00:28:23,243
THEY'VE TRAVELED
OVER A HUNDRED LIGHT YEARS

412
00:28:23,285 --> 00:28:26,997
FROM THEIR HOMEWORLD.

413
00:28:27,039 --> 00:28:31,544
<i>ARCHER'S VOICE: CAPTAIN'S</i>
<i>STARLOG, FEBRUARY 9, 2152.</i>

414
00:28:31,585 --> 00:28:34,796
<i>THE VULCANS HAVE ALLOWED</i>
<i>THE MAZARITES TO LEAVE.</i>

415
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:36,674
<i>AMBASSADOR V'LAR SAYS</i>
<i>THERE'S--</i>

416
00:28:36,714 --> 00:28:39,134
ARCHER AND HIS CREW
MUST'VE TAKEN REFUGE

417
00:28:39,176 --> 00:28:41,761
IN A NEARBY SYSTEM.

418
00:28:41,803 --> 00:28:44,890
THEY MAY INTEND TO RETURN.

419
00:28:44,931 --> 00:28:48,810
WHAT'S THE STATUS
OF THE WARP ENGINES?

420
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:51,771
I'M HAVING DIFFICULTY
WITH THE DILITHIUM MATRIX.

421
00:28:51,813 --> 00:28:55,609
MAKE IT A PRIORITY.

422
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,826
<i>ARCHER'S VOICE: ...2152.</i>

423
00:29:04,868 --> 00:29:06,453
<i>WE'VE RESPONDED</i>
<i>TO A DISTRESS CALL</i>

424
00:29:06,495 --> 00:29:08,414
<i>FROM A VESSEL IN THE...</i>

425
00:29:08,455 --> 00:29:11,917
PHLOX: THEY'RE IMMUNE
TO RADIOLYTIC ISOTOPES.

426
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:14,587
THE STORM WAS NEVER
ANY THREAT TO THEM.

427
00:29:14,628 --> 00:29:16,088
TUCKER: FUNNY.

428
00:29:16,129 --> 00:29:17,506
YOU DIDN'T MENTION THAT.

429
00:29:17,548 --> 00:29:19,007
TAGRIM: WE WERE IN DANGER.

430
00:29:19,049 --> 00:29:20,467
OUR SHIP IS
LESS DURABLE THAN YOURS.

431
00:29:20,509 --> 00:29:21,927
WE WOULD'VE BEEN DESTROYED
BY THE STORM!

432
00:29:21,968 --> 00:29:24,096
WHO ARE THEY?
WHAT ARE THEY DOING HERE?

433
00:29:24,137 --> 00:29:26,348
CAPTAIN, I ASSURE YOU
WE DON'T KNOW THESE MEN.

434
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,392
THEY JUST HAPPENED
TO FIND<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

435
00:29:28,434 --> 00:29:31,478
IN THE MIDDLE OF A CLASS-5
NEUTRONIC STORM?

436
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:33,230
WHERE THREE MEMBERS
OF THEIR OWN SPECIES

437
00:29:33,272 --> 00:29:35,899
JUST<i> HAPPENED</i> TO
BE TAKING REFUGE?

438
00:29:35,941 --> 00:29:38,277
T'POL: WE'RE MORE THAN 20
LIGHT YEARS FROM YOUR HOMEWORLD.

439
00:29:38,318 --> 00:29:40,195
IT'S AN UNLIKELY COINCIDENCE.

440
00:29:40,237 --> 00:29:44,241
ARCHER: I GET THE FEELING
THEY MUST BE LOOKING FOR<i> YOU.</i>

441
00:29:49,246 --> 00:29:50,581
ANSWER ME!

442
00:29:50,623 --> 00:29:52,458
GURI: I TOLD YOU WE SHOULDN'T
HAVE COME HERE.

443
00:29:52,499 --> 00:29:53,917
GURI!

444
00:29:53,959 --> 00:29:56,462
GURI: THEY'RE OFFICERS
OF THE TAKRET MILITIA.

445
00:29:56,503 --> 00:29:58,547
THEY'VE BEEN
PURSUING US FOR WEEKS.

446
00:29:58,589 --> 00:30:00,840
WE THOUGHT WE COULD EVADE THEM
BY HIDING ABOARD YOUR SHIP.

447
00:30:00,882 --> 00:30:02,551
TAKRETI: THEY MUST'VE
DETECTED OUR VESSEL

448
00:30:02,593 --> 00:30:04,762
IN YOUR LAUNCH BAY.

449
00:30:07,931 --> 00:30:09,558
WHAT DO THEY WANT WITH YOU?

450
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:12,018
GURI: WE USED TO BE MEMBERS OF
THE MILITIA IN THE LOWER RANKS,

451
00:30:12,060 --> 00:30:13,437
BUT, AFTER A YEAR,
WE REALIZED

452
00:30:13,479 --> 00:30:14,938
THAT THE COMMANDING
OFFICERS WERE CORRUPT.

453
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:17,524
THEY SEIZE ALIEN VESSELS
WITHOUT PROVOCATION.

454
00:30:17,566 --> 00:30:19,568
THEY MURDER THE CREWS,
TAKE ANYTHING OF VALUE.

455
00:30:19,610 --> 00:30:21,194
TAKRETI: THEY'RE LITTLE MORE
THAN CRIMINALS.

456
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:22,696
TAGRIM: WE TRIED TO RESIGN
OUR COMMISSIONS,

457
00:30:22,738 --> 00:30:24,615
BUT THEY WOULDN'T ALLOW IT.

458
00:30:29,911 --> 00:30:31,955
-YOU'RE DESERTERS.
-WE HAD NO CHOICE.

459
00:30:31,997 --> 00:30:33,582
TAGRIM: WE WOULD'VE TOLD
YOU THE TRUTH,

460
00:30:33,624 --> 00:30:35,959
BUT WE WEREN'T SURE
THAT YOU WOULD HELP US.

461
00:30:36,001 --> 00:30:39,212
GURI: IF THEY FIND US,
WE'LL BE EXECUTED.

462
00:30:39,254 --> 00:30:41,799
TAGRIM: CAPTAIN, I APOLOGIZE
FOR THE DIFFICULT POSITION

463
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:44,718
THAT WE'VE PUT YOU IN,
BUT I KNOW THESE MEN.

464
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:47,304
EVEN IF THEY FOUND US,
I DOUBT THEY'D SIMPLY LEAVE.

465
00:30:47,346 --> 00:30:51,016
THEY'VE CAPTURED VESSELS
FAR LESS IMPRESSIVE THAN YOURS.

466
00:30:51,057 --> 00:30:52,392
REED: THEY'RE TRYING
TO RE-INITIALIZE

467
00:30:52,434 --> 00:30:53,644
THE WARP REACTOR, SIR.

468
00:30:53,686 --> 00:30:55,103
SEEMS TO ME THEY'VE
ALREADY DECIDED

469
00:30:55,145 --> 00:30:56,896
TO HELP THEMSELVES
TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

470
00:30:56,938 --> 00:30:59,149
T'POL: THEY OBVIOUSLY DON'T
REALIZE WE'RE IN THE CATWALK.

471
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:00,859
IF THEY LEARN WE'RE HERE,

472
00:31:00,900 --> 00:31:03,278
IT WOULD UNDOUBTEDLY
ENDANGER THE CREW.

473
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:04,863
TUCKER: WHAT'RE YOU SUGGESTING?

474
00:31:04,904 --> 00:31:06,782
WE JUST SIT ON OUR HANDS

475
00:31:06,824 --> 00:31:08,826
UNTIL THEY FIRE UP THE ENGINES?

476
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:11,370
YOU'RE ASSUMING THESE THREE
ARE TELLING THE TRUTH.

477
00:31:11,411 --> 00:31:12,954
THEY'VE ALREADY LIED TO US.

478
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:14,748
TAGRIM: WE'RE NOT LYING.

479
00:31:14,790 --> 00:31:16,916
THESE MEN ARE DANGEROUS.

480
00:31:25,925 --> 00:31:27,803
Takreti: Paltani to Captain.

481
00:31:27,845 --> 00:31:29,012
YES.

482
00:31:29,054 --> 00:31:30,848
Paltani: The dilithium matrix
is active.

483
00:31:30,889 --> 00:31:32,891
WE'RE READY TO INITIALIZE
THE WARP REACTOR.

484
00:31:32,932 --> 00:31:34,351
Captain: Stand by.

485
00:31:34,393 --> 00:31:35,894
DO WE HAVE HELM CONTROL?

486
00:31:35,935 --> 00:31:38,355
TAKRETI: THE NAVIGATION RELAY
IS STILL NOT RESPONDING.

487
00:31:38,397 --> 00:31:40,524
I THINK THEY'VE BEEN REROUTED.

488
00:31:40,566 --> 00:31:42,025
HOW MUCH LONGER?

489
00:31:42,067 --> 00:31:43,985
TAKRETI: I'M NOT CERTAIN.

490
00:31:44,027 --> 00:31:45,863
CAPTAIN: BRING THE WARP
ENGINES ON LINE

491
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:47,113
and report to the bridge.

492
00:31:47,155 --> 00:31:49,199
ACKNOWLEDGED.

493
00:31:50,283 --> 00:31:51,785
T'POL: WE MAY OUTNUMBER THEM,

494
00:31:51,827 --> 00:31:53,787
BUT WE ONLY HAVE
THREE E.V. SUITS.

495
00:31:53,829 --> 00:31:55,622
REED: I COULD TAKE THE SECURITY
TEAM AND BRING BACK MORE.

496
00:31:55,664 --> 00:31:56,998
TUCKER: I DOUBT YOU'D GET
VERY FAR.

497
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:58,333
THE LAUNCH BAY'S
CRAWLING WITH THEM.

498
00:31:58,375 --> 00:31:59,710
ARCHER: EVEN IF WE COULD
GET THE SUITS,

499
00:31:59,752 --> 00:32:01,461
WE ONLY HAVE 22 MINUTES
IN THE RADIATION.

500
00:32:01,503 --> 00:32:04,297
HARD TO BELIEVE WE COULD
RETAKE THE SHIP IN THAT AM--

501
00:32:11,805 --> 00:32:13,390
ARCHER: HOW LONG DO WE HAVE?

502
00:32:13,432 --> 00:32:15,726
TUCKER: IT'LL TAKE A WHILE
FOR THE WARP COILS TO CHARGE.

503
00:32:15,768 --> 00:32:17,143
ARCHER: HOW LONG?

504
00:32:17,185 --> 00:32:19,730
TUCKER: 20 MINUTES TOPS.

505
00:32:25,985 --> 00:32:28,113
TUCKER: REMEMBER,
JUNCTION 42-ALPHA.

506
00:32:28,154 --> 00:32:29,615
T'POL: UNDERSTOOD.

507
00:32:29,656 --> 00:32:31,700
TUCKER: THIRD PANEL, STARBOARD
SIDE, AND BE CAREFUL.

508
00:32:31,742 --> 00:32:34,661
THERE'S A LOT OF CURRENT RUNNING
THROUGH THOSE CIRCUITS.

509
00:32:36,496 --> 00:32:38,248
I REALLY OUGHT TO BE
THE ONE DOING THIS, CAPTAIN.

510
00:32:38,290 --> 00:32:40,793
THE DOC SAID I WAS ONLY
OUT THERE FOR 13 MINUTES.

511
00:32:40,834 --> 00:32:42,168
ARCHER: FORGET IT, TRIP.

512
00:32:42,210 --> 00:32:43,545
YOU'VE ALREADY BEEN EXPOSED.

513
00:32:43,587 --> 00:32:45,130
HOSHI: I'VE ISOLATED
YOUR COM FREQUENCIES.

514
00:32:45,171 --> 00:32:47,215
THEY WON'T HEAR A THING.

515
00:32:48,258 --> 00:32:50,719
TELL TRAVIS TO
WAIT FOR MY SIGNAL.

516
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:56,642
-ANY PROGRESS?
-NOT YET.

517
00:32:58,268 --> 00:33:00,019
WE COULD LOSE OUR
SHIP BY STAYING HERE.

518
00:33:00,061 --> 00:33:01,563
WE SHOULD TAKE WHAT
WE CAN AND LEAVE.

519
00:33:01,605 --> 00:33:03,022
CAPTAIN: KEEP WORKING!

520
00:33:03,064 --> 00:33:05,734
I WANT HELM CONTROL.

521
00:33:07,486 --> 00:33:09,112
ARCHER: I'LL SEE YOU
BACK AT THE CATWALK.

522
00:33:09,154 --> 00:33:10,363
DON'T BE LATE.

523
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:12,115
REED: AYE, CAPTAIN.

524
00:33:43,355 --> 00:33:44,439
TUCKER: T'POL?

525
00:33:44,481 --> 00:33:45,983
T'Pol: We're in position.

526
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:47,651
ALL RIGHT. FIRST, YOU'RE
GOING TO HAVE TO DISRUPT

527
00:33:47,693 --> 00:33:50,028
THE ANTIMATTER STREAM.

528
00:33:50,069 --> 00:33:51,530
Tucker: Do you see
the blue conduit to the left

529
00:33:51,571 --> 00:33:53,532
of the power-transfer module?

530
00:33:53,573 --> 00:33:54,783
GO AHEAD.

531
00:33:54,825 --> 00:33:56,952
START BY LOCKING DOWN
THE FLOW REGULATORS.

532
00:33:56,994 --> 00:33:59,162
STAND BY.

533
00:34:06,378 --> 00:34:08,588
[ BEEPING ]

534
00:34:13,010 --> 00:34:14,469
WE'RE BEING HAILED.

535
00:34:14,511 --> 00:34:15,679
CAPTAIN: ANOTHER SHIP?

536
00:34:15,721 --> 00:34:18,097
NO.

537
00:34:18,139 --> 00:34:20,433
IT'S COMING
FROM WITHIN THIS VESSEL.

538
00:34:21,518 --> 00:34:23,269
ANSWER IT.

539
00:34:26,565 --> 00:34:28,483
<i>YOU'RE IN MY CHAIR.</i>

540
00:34:28,525 --> 00:34:29,943
CAPTAIN: CAPTAIN ARCHER.

541
00:34:29,985 --> 00:34:32,571
I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU WERE STILL ABOARD.

542
00:34:32,612 --> 00:34:34,698
WHERE'S THE REST OF YOUR CREW?

543
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:36,825
<i>THEY'RE DEAD,</i>

544
00:34:36,867 --> 00:34:38,660
<i>KILLED BY THE STORM.</i>

545
00:34:38,702 --> 00:34:40,286
I'M SORRY.

546
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:42,789
<i>THANKS FOR YOUR CONDOLENCES.</i>

547
00:34:42,831 --> 00:34:44,875
<i>NOW, WHY DON'T YOU...</i>

548
00:34:44,917 --> 00:34:47,210
<i>GET THE HELL OFF MY SHIP?</i>

549
00:34:47,252 --> 00:34:49,713
CAPTAIN: I'M AFRAID
I CAN'T DO THAT.

550
00:34:49,755 --> 00:34:52,215
WE DETECTED A VESSEL
IN YOUR LAUNCH BAY

551
00:34:52,257 --> 00:34:54,300
THAT BELONGS TO
THREE FUGITIVES.

552
00:34:54,342 --> 00:34:56,929
<i>I'VE BEEN WATCHING YOU...</i>

553
00:34:56,970 --> 00:35:00,515
<i>[ GASPING ]</i>

554
00:35:00,557 --> 00:35:03,894
<i>I KNOW YOU'RE TRYING</i>
<i>TO TAKE</i> ENTERPRISE.

555
00:35:03,936 --> 00:35:06,021
<i>I'M NOT GOING TO LET YOU.</i>

556
00:35:06,063 --> 00:35:09,566
YOU'RE IN NO POSITION
TO DO ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

557
00:35:09,608 --> 00:35:12,611
I AM IN COMMAND OF THIS BRIDGE.

558
00:35:12,652 --> 00:35:13,987
YOUR VESSEL HAS BEEN IMPOUNDED

559
00:35:14,029 --> 00:35:16,448
UNDER THE AUTHORITY
OF THE TAKRET MILITIA.

560
00:35:16,489 --> 00:35:18,324
WHEN WE RETURN,
YOU'LL BE CHARGED

561
00:35:18,366 --> 00:35:19,618
WITH CRIMINAL CONSPIRACY.

562
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:21,828
<i>I DON'T RECOGNIZE</i>
<i>YOUR AUTHORITY!</i>

563
00:35:21,870 --> 00:35:24,081
<i>I ANSWER TO STARFLEET COMMAND,</i>

564
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:28,209
<i>AND I'M UNDER ORDERS</i>
<i>TO USE ANY MEANS NECESSARY</i>

565
00:35:28,251 --> 00:35:31,964
<i>TO KEEP MY SHIP</i>
<i>FROM FALLING INTO ENEMY HANDS.</i>

566
00:35:32,005 --> 00:35:35,008
I HAVE SOLDIERS
SEARCHING EVERY DECK.

567
00:35:35,050 --> 00:35:37,886
IT'S ONLY A MATTER OF TIME
BEFORE THEY FIND YOU.

568
00:35:37,928 --> 00:35:40,931
<i>YOU'RE LEAVING ME...</i>

569
00:35:40,973 --> 00:35:43,558
<i>...NO CHOICE.</i>

570
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:46,311
<i>I'LL DESTROY</i> ENTERPRISE.

571
00:35:46,352 --> 00:35:50,189
CAPTAIN: EARTH'S FIRST
WARP-5 STARSHIP?

572
00:35:50,231 --> 00:35:52,400
YOUR FATHER'S ENGINE?

573
00:35:52,442 --> 00:35:54,987
I'VE BEEN READING
ABOUT YOU, CAPTAIN.

574
00:35:55,028 --> 00:35:59,574
I DOUBT VERY MUCH IF YOU'LL DO
ANYTHING TO DAMAGE THIS VESSEL.

575
00:35:59,616 --> 00:36:03,202
<i>YOU'D BE SURPRISED.</i>

576
00:36:03,244 --> 00:36:05,371
CAPTAIN: CAN YOU TRACE
HIS SIGNAL?

577
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:07,040
HE'S SOMEWHERE
ON THE FIFTH DECK.

578
00:36:07,082 --> 00:36:09,626
YOU HAVE MEN THERE.
ALERT THEM.

579
00:36:09,668 --> 00:36:11,503
GO AHEAD.

580
00:36:11,544 --> 00:36:13,797
Archer: It's time
to change course, Travis.

581
00:36:13,839 --> 00:36:15,007
Head straight
for that plasma eddy.

582
00:36:15,048 --> 00:36:16,675
IT'LL TAKE A MINUTE, SIR.

583
00:36:16,716 --> 00:36:18,718
Archer: Try to keep us
in one piece.

584
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:21,680
I'm on my way back.
Archer out.

585
00:36:39,031 --> 00:36:40,115
WE'VE ALTERED COURSE.

586
00:36:40,157 --> 00:36:42,575
CAPTAIN: WHERE'S HE TAKING US?

587
00:36:42,617 --> 00:36:44,953
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM
SHUTTING DOWN THE REACTOR?

588
00:36:44,995 --> 00:36:47,747
WE'RE HAVING TROUBLE
WITH THE DILITHIUM SEQUENCERS.

589
00:36:47,789 --> 00:36:49,457
IT'S TAKING LONGER
THAN WE EXPECTED.

590
00:36:49,499 --> 00:36:50,834
Tucker: I don't mean
to rush you,

591
00:36:50,876 --> 00:36:53,170
BUT IT'S GETTING
PRETTY WARM IN HERE.

592
00:37:13,523 --> 00:37:15,901
HE'S STEERING US
TOWARD A PLASMA EDDY.

593
00:37:15,942 --> 00:37:17,527
CAPTAIN: HOW LONG?

594
00:37:17,569 --> 00:37:19,821
LESS THAN EIGHT MINUTES.

595
00:37:22,074 --> 00:37:23,408
GET ME HELM CONTROL!

596
00:37:23,449 --> 00:37:25,451
IT'LL TAKE ME
MUCH LONGER THAN THAT.

597
00:37:25,493 --> 00:37:26,619
WE SHOULD EVACUATE!

598
00:37:26,661 --> 00:37:28,705
-NO!
-YOU HEARD WHAT HE SAID!

599
00:37:28,747 --> 00:37:31,249
HE'S WILLING
TO DESTROY HIS OWN SHIP!

600
00:37:34,711 --> 00:37:36,796
THE TEMPERATURE JUST WENT UP
ANOTHER SIX DEGREES.

601
00:37:36,838 --> 00:37:38,631
SUBCOMMANDER, HOW'S IT COMING?

602
00:37:38,673 --> 00:37:41,760
T'Pol: We're disabling
the final sequencer.

603
00:37:52,062 --> 00:37:54,313
THE WARP REACTOR HAS SHUT DOWN.

604
00:37:56,108 --> 00:37:57,859
TAKRETI: SPATIAL DISTURBANCE.

605
00:37:57,901 --> 00:38:00,445
WE'RE FOUR MINUTES
FROM THE EDDY.

606
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:25,511
PALANTI: UNLESS YOU'VE FOUND
A WAY TO TURN THIS SHIP AROUND,

607
00:38:25,553 --> 00:38:28,556
I STRONGLY SUGGEST
WE ABORT THE MISSION!

608
00:38:28,598 --> 00:38:30,976
TAKRETI: THREE MINUTES!

609
00:38:32,811 --> 00:38:36,689
CAPTAIN: SOLDIERS, REPORT TO
THE DOCKING HATCH IMMEDIATELY!

610
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:40,944
I REPEAT--
REPORT TO THE DOCKING HATCH!

611
00:38:51,621 --> 00:38:52,956
T'POL: REPORT.

612
00:38:52,998 --> 00:38:54,457
MAYWEATHER: WE'RE TOO CLOSE
TO THE EDDY.

613
00:38:54,499 --> 00:38:57,418
-WE'VE GOT TO VEER OFF.
-MAINTAIN YOUR COURSE.

614
00:39:07,637 --> 00:39:09,347
ANOTHER ONE LIKE THAT
WILL SPLIT US IN TWO.

615
00:39:09,388 --> 00:39:11,683
THEY COULD STILL BE ON BOARD.

616
00:39:11,724 --> 00:39:13,643
WE'VE GOT NO CHOICE.

617
00:39:13,685 --> 00:39:15,645
MAINTAIN YOUR COURSE.
THAT'S AN ORDER.

618
00:39:15,687 --> 00:39:17,438
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

619
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:19,191
T'POL: GO AHEAD.

620
00:39:19,232 --> 00:39:22,568
Archer: Travis, I hope you're
not still heading for that eddy.

621
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:24,529
Our friends are gone.

622
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:26,323
ENSIGN.

623
00:39:46,801 --> 00:39:49,346
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S STARLOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL.

624
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:52,265
WE SEEM TO HAVE PASSED THROUGH
THE WORST PART OF THE STORM,

625
00:39:52,307 --> 00:39:53,474
BUT IT'LL STILL BE A WHILE

626
00:39:53,516 --> 00:39:55,560
BEFORE WE CAN LEAVE
THE CATWALK.

627
00:39:55,601 --> 00:39:57,937
THE CREW'S IN
RELATIVELY GOOD SPIRITS,

628
00:39:57,979 --> 00:39:59,314
CONSIDERING THEY HAVEN'T HAD

629
00:39:59,356 --> 00:40:02,359
A CHANGE OF UNIFORM
IN EIGHT DAYS.

630
00:40:07,072 --> 00:40:09,157
TUCKER: DID THAT GUY SHOOT
ONE OF HIS OWN MEN?

631
00:40:09,199 --> 00:40:12,244
REED: IT'S HARD TO TELL THEM
APART IN THOSE RIDICULOUS HATS.

632
00:40:12,285 --> 00:40:16,289
T'POL: THE DEAD MAN WAS SECRETLY
WORKING FOR SHERIFF BOGGS.

633
00:40:17,623 --> 00:40:18,958
TUCKER: HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

634
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:21,253
T'POL: ISN'T IT OBVIOUS?

635
00:40:23,338 --> 00:40:25,631
Archer: All hands,
this is the Captain.

636
00:40:25,673 --> 00:40:29,177
THANKS TO SOME FINE PILOTING
BY TRAVIS MAYWEATHER,

637
00:40:29,219 --> 00:40:30,929
WE'RE GOING TO BE MOVING OUT
OF THE STORM

638
00:40:30,970 --> 00:40:32,805
A LITTLE EARLIER THAN EXPECTED.

639
00:40:32,847 --> 00:40:34,182
WE SHOULD BE CLEAR
IN A FEW MINUTES.

640
00:40:34,224 --> 00:40:36,601
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

641
00:40:41,564 --> 00:40:43,649
TUCKER: GLAD YOU COULD JOIN US,
SUBCOMMANDER.

642
00:40:43,691 --> 00:40:46,527
WE HAVE MOVIE NIGHT
EVERY TUESDAY...

643
00:40:46,569 --> 00:40:49,322
IF YOU'RE INTERESTED.

644
00:41:13,179 --> 00:41:15,514
TAGRIM: I APOLOGIZE FOR
THE TROUBLE WE'VE CAUSED.

645
00:41:15,556 --> 00:41:18,059
WHERE YOU HEADED NEXT?

646
00:41:18,101 --> 00:41:20,019
TAGRIM: THE GYRANNAN SYSTEM.

647
00:41:20,061 --> 00:41:22,314
WE SHOULD BE SAFE THERE.

648
00:41:22,355 --> 00:41:24,857
GOOD LUCK.

649
00:41:36,202 --> 00:41:38,746
THAT'S EVERYONE.
